As REQUESTED, JOHANN finished his story the fol\f1\-\f0 lowing evening. Both women wept with him as he de\f1\-\f0 scribed Maria\rquote s birth and Beatrice\rquote s death. Sister Nuba was fascinated by Whiteland. She interrupted several times, asking Johann to supply more details. When Johann ad\f1\-\f0 nutted being confused and somewhat bitter about being returned to the island, Sister Nuba made an uncharacteris\f1\-\f0 tically long speech.\par
\ldblquote Whiteland was a part of heaven, Brother Johann,\rdblquote  she said. \ldblquote And Beatrice and all the other glowing figures you encountered were angels. There\rquote s no other possible expla\f1\-\f0 nation that makes ....... - You are a most fortunate man, Brother Johann, to have made a visit to heaven during your lifetime, while your soul is still inside the limitations of your body What a rare privilege you have had. God must still have some extraordinary work for you to accomplish. Do not feel sorrow because you were returned to what we call the real world. Rejoice that you have been granted a glisnpse of heaven\rdblquote\par
