\pard\fi720\sl-243\slmult0\qj\tx9291 EVERYONE EXCEPT SISTER Nuba, who stayed in the village with the children, left the village to search for Satoko within an hour after Fernando informed them that she had disappeared. Vivien and Kwame followed the path through the forest that led eventually back to the lake. Ravi and Anna headed one way along the rim of the chasm, while Brother Jose went with Fernando in the opposite direction.\par
\pard\fi720\sl-238\slmult0\qj\tx9291 They gathered back at the village late that afternoon. Nobody had found any clue that suggested where Sato\f1\-\f0 ko might have gone. Fernando was beside himself with grief. He asked the group to help him look for her again the next day, and they all assented. But the second day, with everyone searching a new and different area around their village, was equally fruitless. There were no signs of Satoko anywhere.\par
By this time everyone except Fernando had come to the same conclusion. \ldblquote The only explanation that makes any sense," Vivien said softly to Kwame as they were strolling along the path with their children, \ldblquote is that Satoko jumped into the chasm very soon after she departed. Otherwise we would have found something. She wasn\rquote t in the frame of mind that she would deliberately have con\f1\-\f0 cealed her route?\par
\ldblquote I agree," Kwame answered. \ldblquote I\rquote ve been thinking about it all day. But how do we tell Fernando to give up hope? He is obviously expecting us to continue the search yet another\par
day Meanwhile, it is time for us to harvest the grain from the northwestern farms?\rquote\par
Fernando was not pleased the next morning when Kwame informed him that only BrotherJose was available to continue looking for Satoko. His eyes glazed from weeping and lack of sleep, Fernando announced that he would \i never \i0 give up searching for Satoko and that he in\f1\-\f0 tended personally to cover every square meter of their do\f1\-\f0 main. He was true to his word. In the month that followed Fernando was rarely present in the village. He would stay away for two days, then thee, as his search for Satoko cov\f1\-\f0 ered territory more and more distant from the village.\par
To keep Keiko from feeling completely abandoned, Vivien and Kwame essentially adopted her during this pe\f1\-\f0 riod. Keiko and Beatrice became inseparable. When Fer\f1\-\f0 nando did return to the village, he was usually too exhausted or distraught to pay much attention to his daughter. After her father\rquote s brief visits, Keilco would crawl silently into Kwame\rquote s comforting arms.\par
Late one evening Fernando came back, after having been gone for almost four days, with some surprising news. He had worked his way though the thick, nearly impene\f1\-\f0 trable forest on the far side of their domain. On the other end of that forest, he had discovered a spot where the chasm was so narrow that Fernando had been able to jump across to the other side. He had explored over there for two days. Fernando reported that it was an exciting and won\f1\-\f0 derfiil paradise full of fruit trees, vines, bubbling streams, and cascading waterfalls. He even brought back a large, new, purple fruit, the size of a basketball, that was ab\f1\-\f0 solutely delicious.\par
In spite of Kwanie\rquote s suggestion that they should be cautious, and ask themselves why this other land had so deliberately been hidden from them, the village con\f1\-\f0 sensus was that an expedition should be sent immediately to explore this new realm across the chasm, both to see if perhaps Satoko might be there and to learn more about it. BrotherJose was selected to go with Fernando.\par
\pard\fi720\sl-243\slmult0\qj\tx9291 They were gone for six days. During their absence a euphoric optimism swept through the community Vivien es\f1\-\f0 pecially was carried away by her own fantasies of a more\par
teresting place to live. After eight years, she told herself, there were finally going to be some real changes in their lives. Vivien couldn\rquote t wait for Fernando and BrotherJose to return.\par
