Johann used these conversations with the ghosts of his past and his many projects to chase away the demons of de\-pression. \ldblquote I will endure:\rquote  he said quietly to the adoclyne cleaning his cell one day. The alien did not even look at him. It simply retracted the scoop from the hole in the rock floor and emptied the contents into the container. Johann took three steps away from the wall, toward the nozzler. It stopped what it was doing, without dropping the scoop it was holding in its elevated claw, and both the two forward eyes looked at Johann.\f2\par
