HE KNEW WHEN he reached the edge of Black Rock Promontory and gazed down at where the village had once been that there was no chance anyone had been left alive. Nevertheless, clutching the amulet and necklace in his hand, Johann descended into the area and spent several hours searching through the debris.\par
Just as at their village, the brankers had removed almost everything. But Johann did find \f3 one of Maria\rquote s \f2 handmade skirts, and an outfit for Stephanie. Under a large rock in the middle of the path through the village, he also found a piece of bark on which a note had been hastily scribbled.\par
\f3\ldblquote You were right, Johann. \f2 Thanks for saving Stephanie. I have always loved \f3 you.\rdblquote\f2\par
